narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: A lot about dealing with atonal music. I improved my sightsinging and ear a lot.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: In class activities are good, but I felt they were a little repetitive.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: It's a very chill class if you know a little about music, but it definitely draws a crowd of people who REALLY know music, but it's not required for the class, so if you just enjoy music and are comfortable in the presence of people who live it even if you don't, it'll be a good time.

I really wish this course were way more intense. The class was very lax and low-key in a way that I thought would have been more fitting of a lower-level class, given that this is the department's most advanced musicianship class. I think the class could make an effort to challenge its students a lot more.
